      <div style="overflow: auto;">
       <p style="white-space: pre-wrap;">
        @minutiae: this is a bit more advanced than the examples I presented in the article. Association tables can have extra fields besides the id fields create the mappings of the the many-to-many relationship. You could add a field to the 'followers' association table that indicates if a relationship is a favorite or not. You can then use that field to sort the posts results.
       </p>
