       </span>
       said
       <span class="flask-moment" data-format="fromNow(0)" data-refresh="0" data-timestamp="2013-03-03T02:19:43Z">
        2013-03-03T02:19:43Z
       </span>
      </p>
      <div style="overflow: auto;">
       <p style="white-space: pre-wrap;">
        @George: I haven't tried it, and you don't say what's the error that you get, but I think the secondary join expression needs to be (likes.c.artistliked == Artist.id). You are saying just "id" on the right side which is interpreted as User.id because you are in the context of the User class. Also note that when you are doing a many-to-many between two pretty standard models like yours you do not need to specify primary and secondary join expressions, those are automatically determined by SQLAlchemy. See "http://pythonhosted.org/Flask-SQLAlchemy/models.html#many-to-many-relationships" for an example.
       </p>
      </div>
     </div>
